name: Studentenverzeichnis LMU (1876) v2
content:
The attached page contains a table of students at LMU Munich.
The table columns visible in the page are ["Namen.", "Heimath", "Wohnung", "Studium"].
- "Namen." contains "Last Names, First Names", e.g., "Mustermann, Max Joseph"
- "Heimath" contains the city of origin and the state of origin, e.g., "Kassel   Hessen" or "Athen  Griechenland" or "München  Bayern". In the output JSON, separate these into "Heimath_Stadt" and "Heimath_Land", respectively. This field frequently contain a ditto (") symbol. Extract this faithfully as the ditto symbol itself.
- "Wohnung" which contains an address, e.g., "Schellingstr. 5/2", or a place, e.g., "Maximilianeum". Pay careful attention that the "Heimath_Land" is not extracted into the "Wohnung" field.
- "Studium" which contains the subject of study, e.g., "Medizin". This can be abbreviated.

Extract the data in table into the target JSON structure.

name: Heiratsurkunden Feldmoching
content:
The attached page contains a table of marriages certified.
The table columns are {"Familienname", "Vornamen", "Name des anderen Ehegatten", "geb. am", "Fam. Buch Nr."].

Extract the data into the target JSON structure. Don't hallucinate.
